===Etymology===
From {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|scyrte|lang=ang}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{term/t|gem-pro|*skurtijǭ}}.  Cognate with Dutch {{term|schort|lang=nl}}, German {{term|Schürze||apron|lang=de}}. {{term|skirt|Skirt|lang=en}} is a parallel formation from Old Norse; compare also {{term|short|lang=en}}, from the same ultimate source.

